  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Science, Technology, Mathematics and Engineering Mathematics Teacher Education (IRIS CONNECT software)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to build strong research and innovation nations, there must be a steady supply of talented students equipped with the knowledge, skills and desire to follow a career in Science, Engineering, Technology and Maths (STEM).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support dialogue and knowledge exchange between the UK and South Africa around Science, Technology, Mathematics and Engineering (STEM) education approaches for improved curricula for primary, secondary and tertiary STEM education.
&#x2022; Support development of new and improved pedagogies and teaching and learning resources, relevant to South African context and development need, leading to enhanced capacity for teaching STEM subjects.
&#x2022; Support centres of excellence for STEM education in South Africa through partnerships with UK experts.
&#x2022; Equip students with a better understanding and appreciation of STEM education in an international context

This will mean more students with relevant skills and knowledge pursue a STEM-related career, thus building absorptive capacity for research and innovation in country.</narrative>
  </description>
